galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Hatterene
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches. It is known as the Forest Witch.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Impidimp
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It sneaks into people's homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Morgrem
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: With a single swing of its spear-like hair, it can pierce a foe's heart. It is a fiendish Pokémon.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Grimmsnarl
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: With the hair on its body, it can create a muscle-like structure that is stronger than a wrestler's.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Obstagoon
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It is a master of taunting and provocation. Its voice is loud enough to stun a foe.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Perrserker
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It has a violent and barbaric nature. The hardened hair on its body forms a natural helmet and armor.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Cursola
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Its soul is overflowing with spectral energy. It is said that its body is a home for wandering spirits.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Sirfetch'd
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Only the Sirfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When its leek withers, it will retire from fighting.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Mr. Rime
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It is a master of tap dancing. It can produce a psychic field from the ice on its belly.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Runerigus
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Milcery
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Evolves into Alcremie by spinning around with a Sweet.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Alcremie
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it has decorated with cream.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Falinks
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Pincurchin
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It stores electricity in its spines. If it is attacked, it will shoot its spines at its attacker.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Snom
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft, freshly fallen snow.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Evolves into Frosmoth with high Happiness at night.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Frosmoth
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing blizzards to chase offenders away.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Stonjourner
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Eiscue
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It keeps its head iced constantly to keep it cool. It can produce cold air from its head.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Final Stage. Can change from Ice Face to Noice Face form.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Indeedee
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. It is a very intelligent Pokémon.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Final Stage. Has different movepools and stats based on gender.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Morpeko
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they're precious treasures. It is always hungry.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Final Stage. Can change between Full Belly and Hangry Mode.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Cufant
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It is a very strong Pokémon, able to carry a load of 1,000 pounds.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Copperajah
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It is proud of its trunk, which is strong enough to crush boulders.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Dracozolt
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Arctozolt
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: The shaking of its ice-covered snout can generate electricity. It lived in a time beforeucus.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Dracovish
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can't breathe unless it's underwater.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Arctovish
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It can freeze its foes with its freezing breath, which is said to be as cold as -580 degrees Fahrenheit.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Duraludon
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Dreepy
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: If this weak Pokémon is by itself, a mere child could defeat it. But if Dreepy has friends to help it, it can evolve and become much stronger.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Drakloak
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It can fly at speeds exceeding 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy that it keeps on its head.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Dragapult
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Zacian
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Legendary. Can change to Crowned Sword form by holding a Rusted Sword.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Zamazenta
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master's Shield. It was feared and respected by all.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Legendary. Can change to Crowned Shield form by holding a Rusted Shield.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Eternatus
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Kubfu
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: This Pokémon is a master of the martial arts. It is said that its every motion is graceful and beautiful.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Evolves into Urshifu after training in the Tower of Darkness or Tower of Waters.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Urshifu
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: This Pokémon is a master of the martial arts. It is said that its every motion is graceful and beautiful.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Final Stage. Has Single Strike (Fighting/Dark) and Rapid Strike (Fighting/Water) Styles.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Zarude
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It can grow vines from the back of its neck, its wrists, and the soles of its feet. The vines are strong and flexible.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Regieleki
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It’s said that removing the rings on Regieleki’s body will unleash the Pokémon’s latent power.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Regidrago
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago’s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory remains unproven.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Glastrier
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It has a ruthless nature. It will take anything it wants by force.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Spectrier
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It is a swift and powerful Pokémon. It is said that its kicks can separate a soul from its body.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Calyrex
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It is a merciful Pokémon, able to bring forth lush vegetation and heal the sick and wounded.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Legendary. Can mount Glastrier or Spectrier with the Reins of Unity.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Wyrdeer
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: The black orbs at the bases of its antlers are spheres of psychic energy. It is a very intelligent Pokémon.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Kleavor
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the Hisui region. Its body is as hard as stone.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Ursaluna
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It is said that it can travel through the dimensions. It is a very powerful Pokémon.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Basculegion
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It is possessed by the souls of other Basculin that have perished. It is a very aggressive Pokémon.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Sneasler
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Its claws are tipped with a potent poison. It can climb walls with its sharp claws.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Overqwil
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: Its spikes are hard as steel. It is a very aggressive Pokémon.

galar_pokedex_part_2.name: Enamorus
galar_pokedex_part_2.description: It is a Pokémon that has been sealed away for a long time. It is said that its love can bring life back to a barren land.
galar_pokedex_part_2.evolution: Legendary. Can change to Therian Forme with a Reveal Glass.
